; Plugin differential harness fixture: implicit_prices when a posting
; has BOTH a cost spec AND a price annotation. Annotation wins; the
; plugin must emit exactly ONE price (not two).
;
; Pre-#997 this fixture would have surfaced the double-emit bug.

plugin "beancount.plugins.implicit_prices"

2024-01-01 open Assets:Brokerage
2024-01-01 open Assets:Cash
2024-01-01 open Income:CapitalGains
2024-01-01 commodity HOOL

; Buy first so we have a lot to sell against
2024-01-10 * "Buy stock"
  Assets:Brokerage  10 HOOL {520 USD}
  Assets:Cash  -5200 USD


; The 100 USD discrepancy between cost basis (5×520) and sale price
; (5×540) is the realized gain — beancount expects either explicit
; routing to an Income:CapitalGains account or auto-balance with
; Equity:Earnings:Current.
2024-01-15 * "Sell at price (with cost basis)"
  Assets:Brokerage     -5 HOOL {520 USD} @ 540 USD
  Assets:Cash        2700 USD
  Income:CapitalGains -100 USD
